TI  - Encapsulation, dehydration and cryoprotection in regenerative capacity of shoot apices of Genipa americana
T2  - CIENCIA RURAL
AB  - Genipa americana (genipap) is a forest species belonging to the Rabiaceae family that has economic and environmental importance, being valued for food production, recuperation of degraded areas, in the composition in areas of permanent preservation and agroforestry. The objective of this research was to evaluate the effect of different times of dehydration in laminar flow cab and immersion time in ciyoprotecting solution (MS+0.5M sucrose) on the regenerative capacity of shoot apices for establishing future cryopreservation protocols. The shoot apices were obtained from seedlings, of Oiteiros accession, germinated and cultured in vitro. Explants were subjected to encapsulation and different exposure times in cryoprotecting solution and dehydration in a laminar flow cab. The ciyoprotection and dehydration does not modijr the viability of the shoot apices of genipap encapsulated or unencapsulated. Immersion for 24 hours in cryoprotecting solution and the dehydration in a laminar flow cab by 2 hours have potential for use in future studies of ciyopreservation by encapsulation-dehydration.
