AB  - The article discusses the results of research on radiometric processing of multitemporal satellite images in order to monitor deforestation in the Amazon region. Images acquired by Landsat ETM+ and CBERS-2 were used. The proposed algorithms enabled an objective analysis of deforestation and regeneration distribution within tropical rainforests. The advantage of the method is its simple algorithm and lack of need for atmospheric correction.
