AU  - DOBEREINER, J
TI  - OCCURRENCE OF AZOSPIRILLUM AMAZONENSE IN SOME AMAZONIAN ECOSYSTEMS
T2  - REVISTA DE MICROBIOLOGIA
AB  - A survey was made of the occurrence in the Amazon region of the recently described N2-fixing bacterium A. amazonense. Samples were examined from soils and plant roots collected in natural ecosystems and in cultivated areas. The bacterium was frequently found in Gramineae and some other species in low land soils (varzea), and in an established Brachiaria humidicola pasture. A. amazonense and other N2-fixing bacteria were found only sporadically in degradated pasture, regenerating forest (campina) and in virgin forest (floresta de terra firme). Comparative counts with the known Azospirillum spp. and with Beijerinckia revealed higher numbers of A. amazonense in roots of a palm tree (Bactris gasipaes) and a grass (B. humidicola).
